Mr. Burns, the head of the newly formed Special Corps, is a man of rigid posture and even more rigid principles. His authority is absolute, his demeanor austere. Beneath a veneer of icy professionalism, a volatile temper simmers, ready to erupt at the slightest provocation.

He views the world with a cynical eye, seeing only threats and opportunities for control. The rise of unknown monsters and the instability of the modern world are merely pieces on the chessboard, opportunities for influence and the expansion of his power.
